INSERT INTO `field_guide_entry` VALUES (1,'celestial','Bivu','bivu','Only two writings about Bivu remain today, so relatively little is known about her.\n\nThe first is in a list of Gizubi\'s children. Many such lists have been discovered, and many children appear in multiple such lists, however Bivu\'s name is mentioned in only one: the Tussaud Tablet. This tablet is unique for being the only one known to include the names of many of Gizubi\'s children\'s mothers, however Bivu is among the few whose mothers are not specified.\n\nThe second mention of Bivu is found in a collection of creation stories, where she causes a star\'s explosion by making love to it.',NULL),(2,'celestial','Cosmic Goat','cosmic-goat','The Cosmic Goat soars over the near Umbra with the winds and waves of energy given off by the barrier separating this world from the other. From its udder flows never-ending streams of milk, which form the rivers that feed into the White Lake.\r\n\r\nPatrons of the Cosmic Goat believe that the White Lake sits at the very center of the universe, and that everything springs from it. They protect the lake from anyone, thing, or force that might damage it.','[\"access to the Umbra\"]'),(3,'location','Burnt Forest','burnt-forest','Valnötvale was home to many faefolk before a meteor materialized overhead, struck at its center, and burrowed into the earth.\r\n\r\nMany trees were immediately destroyed by the shock wave; many more were set alight by a fire that spread across the valley, reducing it to embers and ash.\r\n\r\nMost of the fae that survived fled to neighboring kingdoms, which now call the place \"the Burnt Forest\". But a few refused to leave. They continue to live in this place, fighting the fires that still spring up from time to time, tending to the saplings that grow amidst the ashes, and believing in a new Valnötvale.',NULL),(4,'location','Le Manoir de Chocolat','manoir-chocolat','A strange manor located... _somewhere_ on the island. Pets with Chocolate Keys have no trouble traveling to and from the place, but no human has been able to find it. Pets won\'t go when followed, and GPS isn\'t available on the island, so tracking the pets isn\'t currently possible.\n\nAt least one project is in development to try and track the pets using custom hardware, but custom parts are needed, and supply ships only come twice a year, so progress has been slow.',NULL),(5,'celestial','Drizzly Bear','drizzly-bear','These creatures live in the shadowy woods of the near umbra, bathing in its rivers, and hunting smaller spirits for Quintessence.\r\n\r\nAfter a bath, a Drizzly Bear will often shake itself dry, sending droplets of water into the material world. Some cosmologers estimate that Drizzly Bears are responsible for 10-20% of Earth\'s rainfall, mostly in the form of light drizzles and sunshowers.',NULL),(6,'animal','Huge Toad','huge-toad','Many Huge Toads inhabit the island. They dwell in dimly-lit areas, and have a unique species of Toadstool growing on their backs. Whether the relationship between these two species is symbiotic or parasitic is still unknown, and the complete life-cycles of both species is still an area of active research.\n\nWhat _is_ known is that this species of Toadstool is particularly potent.','[]'),(7,'location','Shipwrecked Fleet','shipwreck','A fleet of ships lie scattered on the sea floor around the island. Their origin is unknown, but they are estimated to be between 2000 and 3000 years old.','[\"access to the deep sea\"]'),(8,'animal','Whales','whales','Whales can often be seen coming up for air around the island. On some nights, their songs are carried over the island by warm winds, softly audible to any awake.','[\"access to the deep sea\"]'),(9,'celestial','Infinity Imp','infinity-imp','These ne\'er-do-wells will sometimes show up when trying to resolve infinities in mathematical formulae and proofs. Many mathematicians - on the brink of a solution - have lost their train of thought while trying to fight one of these off.',NULL),(10,'plant','Mysterious Plant','mysterious-plant','This plant is capable of producing all manner of fruit, from Fluff and Beans, to Tentacles and Mermaid Eggs. There are even rumors of Mysterious Plants growing ears and eyes, which are said to feed information to Noetala in the form of dreams, allowing her to learn about the world even while she slumbers.\n\nIt may come as no surprise that this terrifying plant is closely related to another cursed nightshade: the aubergine.',NULL),(11,'location','Sea of Dreams','sea-of-dreams','The waters of the Sea of Dreams are dreams given form. Without special protection, any creature, person, or even god who looks at its surface will immediately fall asleep.\n\nA warrior named Sabriscille once entered the Sea of Dreams in order to enter the dreams of a Tarasque and learn its weakness, but she spent so long in the sea she became part of it. When she finally found the Terasque\'s dream, it woke up; the dream evaporated, and with it, so did Sabriscille.',NULL),(12,'location','Île Volcan','ile-volcan','The first recorded discovery of Poppy Seed Pets island is by French explorers in the early 1500s, by the ship HMS Grand Rapace. According to the captain\'s log, its volcano was in the midst of an eruption, so the crew did not go ashore. They named the island \"Île Volcan\" - Volcano Island - observed it for a couple days, and moved on.\r\n\r\nThe second recorded exploration of the island is by a Russian ship in the mid 1720s, captained by Chestibor Grankin. According to Grankin\'s logs, they had received special orders directly from the Emperor, Peter the Great, to establish a presence on the island. Russia had apparently learned of the island\'s existence through the Spanish, however somewhere along the line \"Île Volcan\" had been misunderstood to be the name of the island\'s volcano, and not of the island itself.\r\n\r\nPeter the Great died in 1725, possibly while Grankin\'s ship was still at sea. Unaware of the Emperor\'s death, Grankin and his crew continued their mission, and established a small settlement on the island. However, a couple years later, they all died of unknown causes. Remains of their settlement, as well as several unusual clockwork installations, can still be found on the island today.\r\n\r\n_(Your pets may now go looking for ruined settlements.)_','[\"protection from heat\"]'),(13,'location','Coral Reef','coral-reef','A coral reef encircles the southern end of the island. It is home to a diverse ecosystem, including a species of Hammerhead unique to the island. Like many reefs around the world, it is also beginning to show signs of damage due to rising global temperatures.',NULL),(14,'location','Cryovolcano','cryovolcano','Cryovolcanoes - found on many icy moons and planets - are a type of volcano that erupts volatiles such as water, ammonia, or methane, rather than molten rock.\r\n\r\nOn planets with subsurface oceans, cryovolcanoes may bring the liquids of those oceans to the surface. If those oceans are home to living creatures, they, or their waste and byproducts, could also be brought to the surface in the eruptions.\r\n\r\nSCIENCE!',NULL),(15,'celestial','Nang Tani','nang-tani','The ghost of a young woman, Nang Tani lives among banana trees, and can sometimes be seen on a full moon. Her skin is greenish, and her lips have the color of a ripe gourd.\r\n\r\nNang Tani is a friendly spirit that sometimes gives food to travelers, and harms men who have wronged women.',NULL),(16,'cryptid','Argopelter','argopelter','This ape-like creature lives in hollow trees, feeding on birds and rotten wood. From high up in the branches, it enjoys throwing branches at unsuspecting passersby.\r\n\r\nIt gives birth to litters which always have an odd number of pups, and are always delivered on the 29th of February.','[]'),(17,'location','Tell Samarzhoustia','tell-samarzhoustia','Not much is known about the city state of Tell Samarzhoustia, other than what has been told to us by its traveling merchants, among whom boasting appears to be a common personality trait.\r\n\r\nIf the information we\'ve been told is true, Tell Samarzhoustia is a prosperous, underwater city state, inhabited by - or at least visited by - creatures from many places. Its upper class appears to consist predominantly of a race of bipedal fish who refer to themselves as Tell Samarzhoustians; whether this is a species name, or a term which applies to any inhabitant of Tell Samrzhoustia is unclear.\r\n\r\nThere is no known form of currency that is not accepted in Tell Samarzhoustia, and its grand markets deal not only in goods, but in information and technology.\r\n\r\nTell Samarzhoustian merchants occasionally speak of the other city states they deal with; among those, the Eridanus Federation appears to be held in great esteem.',NULL),(18,'ceremony','Trick-or-treating','trick-or-treating','Though we have been observing the planet for some time, we were all surprised by the tradition of trick-or-treating, which, we learned, takes place once every Earth year.\n\nThe custom involves humans - typically the young - dressing up in costumes and going from house to house, knocking on doors and asking for energy-dense foods by uttering the phrase \"trick or treat.\"\n\nOur initial reaction was one of puzzlement: why would human young go through the trouble of dressing up in costumes and going door-to-door for food? They have many other, simpler means of acquiring food. After further investigation we discovered at least some answers.\n\nThere is an ancient Earth festival called \"Samhain\", a celebration of the end of the harvest season and the beginning of winter. During this festival, humans would light bonfires and wear costumes to ward off \"evil spirits\".\n\nIt\'s not entirely clear how, but it appears this tradition evolved into the modern practice of trick-or-treating. The phrase \"trick or treat\", at one time, was a threat of mischievous acts if the homeowners didn\'t give out treats; we speculate that it is a form of food sacrifice to appease the \"evil spirits\", a behavior which we have observed in a handful of other human traditions.\n\nThough there are aspects we are still unclear on, we conclude that the tradition of trick-or-treating is, ultimately, harmless.\n\nIt seems we still have much to learn about this place.',NULL),(19,'celestial','Hun-Came','hun-came','A devious lord of the underworld, most infamous for his involvement in the murder of the twins Hun Hunahpu and Vucub Hunahpu.\n\nHun-Came tricked the twins into completing a series of impossibly-dangerous tasks. They repeatedly failed, becoming badly-wounded, until Hun-Came killed them outright, decapitating them.\n\nHun Hunahpu\'s wife, unknowingly impregnated by spit from her husband\'s decapitated head, later gave birth to twins of her own. These twins avenged their parents by killing Hun-Came, along with many other death gods, becoming known as the Hero Twins.\n\nBut though this all took place thousands of years ago, disciples of Hun-Came still remain, carrying on his evil will...',NULL),(20,'location','The Hollow Earth','hollow-earth','When Edmond Halley wasn\'t looking for comets, he was also looking for an explanation as to why the Earth\'s magnetic poles drifted over time. His proposal was that the Earth might be composed of concentric, rotating, hollow spheres, and that as those spheres turned, they pulled at the Earth\'s magnetic field.\n\nSince then, numerous explorers have attempted to find entrances to the inside of the Earth. When the Portal was first discovered on Poppy Seed Pets island, the \"theory\" that the Earth might be hollow rose dramatically in popularity. Today, it\'s estimated that a worrying 10-15% of people now believe the Earth to actually be hollow!\n\nIn the scientific community, the two dominant theories surrounding the Portal are: 1. that it\'s a wormhole to some distant location, and evidence that negative mass may be physically possible, or 2. that it\'s an opening into some unfurled dimensions of space, and evidence in support of 11-dimensional String Theory.\n\nWhatever the case, it seems you\'ve also found one inside your house.\n\nSo that\'s neat.',NULL),(21,'cryptid','Onion Boy','onion-boy','This small creature is sometimes spotted near the edge of town, wrapped in tattered paper and cloth, scavenging for trinkets and food. No one\'s gotten a good look at one yet, partially because of the terrible, onion-like odor that surrounds them.','[]'),(22,'synthetic','Abandondero','abandondero','This synthetic lifeform is thought to be the decaying remains of robot workers left behind by aliens in the Hollow Earth... but if that\'s true, what are they doing in the Umbra? And armed!','[\"access to the Umbra\"]'),(23,'location','The Umbra','umbra','The Umbra consists of all the things in the universe that are at the edge of human knowledge and understanding. The closest part of it is a shadowy reflection of the human world, with all the forests, buildings, and other objects that have been destroyed, but are still remembered. Further out is the Land of the Dead, the Sea of Dreams, and other places of recent memory and imagination. At its furthest reaches, The Umbra resembles deep space, twinkling with cosmic strings, unknown gods, and other things that only a handful of humans have ever imagined.\r\n\r\nTo get to the Umbra, one must pass through the Storm - a swirling cacophony of energy that takes great skill to enter and navigate. This separation makes the Umbra a favorable place to live for creatures that humanity has difficulty accepting, including werewolves, vampires, and even other humans who have learned to wield true magic.',NULL);
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `field_guide_entry` ENABLE KEYS */;
UNLOCK TABLES;

