mbining a four-sided and a six-sided. I mean, you can\'t roll a 1 by rolling a four and six-sided die combined, right? (And don\'t even get me _started_ on bell curves...)\r\n\r\nNo, if you want larger dice, the only logical thing to do is to make smaller dice larger, like with some Megalium, or something.\r\n\r\n_Only_ logical thing. _Totally_ logical. Not a single contradiction or flaw to be found...','die/d10','[[\"Roll\", \"die/#/roll\"]]',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1160,'Glowing Twelve-sided Die','You\'re probably asking yourself \"why aren\'t there any fourteen-sided dice? Or sixteen-sided? Or just five-sided?\"\r\n\r\nThe dice available in Poppy Seed Pets are limited to those for which there are platonic solids. The non-platonic solids seemed a little risque to include, even for Poppy Seed Pets.','die/d12','[[\"Roll\", \"die/#/roll\"]]',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1161,'Marshmallows',NULL,'dessert/marshmallows','[]',NULL,412,5,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1162,'S\'more','Who was the first person to taste a s\'more, do you think? Did they have any earthly notion of what they were about to experience? They must have been so-- uh... what\'s the opposite of \"disappointed\"? \"Appointed\"? They must have been so... that thing.','dessert/smore',NULL,NULL,413,15,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1163,'Treat of Crispy Rice',NULL,'dessert/crispy-rice-treat','[]',NULL,414,7,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1164,'Dicerca','This beetle-inspired mask can bring a snazzy new look to any face! Of course, some pets wear masks on their butts instead of their faces; fortunately, this beetle-inspired mask can bring a snazzy new look to any butt, too!','hat/dicerca',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,100,0,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1165,'The Beginning of the Armadillos',NULL,'book/armadillos','[[\"Read\", \"theBeginningOfTheArmadillos/#/read\"]]',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,120,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1166,'High Tide',NULL,'trinket/high-tide',NULL,375,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,7,105,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,10),(1167,'Tiny Rocketship','In the depths of space, where the stars shine bright\r\nThere was a tiny rocket ship that soared with all its might\r\n\r\nIt flew through the air with the greatest of ease\r\nPast the stars and the moon, and through the Milky Way\'s seas\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\nRoko, Skye. \"Tiny Rocket Ship\". <cite>Voyages to the Stars: Poetic Journeys from the Unknown</cite>, edited by Penelope Roberts and Jake Mitchell, Inkwell Imprints, 2055, pp. 149','hat/tiny-rocketship',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,173,0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1168,'Sharktooth Axe',NULL,'tool/axe/sharktooth',NULL,377,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,7,106,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,10),(1169,'Iron Axe',NULL,'tool/axe/iron',NULL,378,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1170,'Quill','Is there such a thing as a rhetorical _answer_?\n\nNo, that wasn\'t a rhetorical question!','tool/quill/feather','[]',380,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,10,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1171,'Short-range Telephone','Not entirely dissimilarly to the modern smartphone, the short-range telephone has a surprising number of uses.','tool/telephone/short-range',NULL,381,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,4,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1172,'Jelling Polyp',NULL,'animal/meat/jelling-polyp','[[\"\\\"Hatch\\\"?\", \"egg/jellingPolyp/#/hatch\"]]',NULL,415,24,NULL,174,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1173,'Gnome\'s Favor',NULL,'treasure/gnomish-deal','[[\"Get Quintessence\", \"gnomesFavor/#/quint\"], [\"Get Food\", \"gnomesFavor/#/food\"], [\"Get Treasure\", \"gnomesFavor/#/treasure\"]]',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,285,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1174,'No Right Turns','\"Who invented right and left, and what\'s it for?\" ~Fern Brady','tool/axe/no-right-turns','[]',382,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1175,'Purple Corn','What?! \"Can you make Purple Corn by dying yellow Corn purple?\"!!? Don\'t be ridiculous! You have to grow it, just like any other Corn!\r\n\r\n