ntary form of telepathy, capable of projecting emotions and simple urges into the minds of those nearby. Subjects report feeling sensations of anger, hunger, and an overwhelming desire to use S. Epée in acts of violence. These effects are significantly diminished in the presence of lead, suggesting that S. Epée\'s psychic abilities are susceptible to standard psychic dampening measures.\"','tool/sword/epee-ess',NULL,461,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,10),(1383,'Lox','Gravlax is a kind of Lox, not a kind of Pokémon.\n\nDon\'t feel bad: it\'s a common misconception.','animal/meat/lox',NULL,NULL,507,8,NULL,256,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1384,'Pommegranite','This strange fruit from the Umbra is not safe to eat. Some people say it\'s an aphrodisiac, but those people say that about, like, _everything_.','fruit/pommegranite','[[\"Smash\", \"pommegranite/#/smash\"]]',NULL,NULL,14,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1385,'Monday Coin','\"Well this one is pretty: Monday... Moon... you get it.\" ~Kat','coin/moon',NULL,462,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1386,'Tuesday Coin','\"Tuesday is named for an ancient god of the sky. I can never remember how to spell his name >_> Anyway: so it\'s got a cloud, and a little wind... thing... I guess? 🤷‍♀️ Why not.\" ~Kat','coin/tiwaz',NULL,463,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1387,'Wednesday Coin','\"Wednesday is named after Woden, who\'s kind of similar to Odin. I don\'t know why there\'s two opposite-pointing triangles on his coin, though. Weird.\" ~Kat','coin/woden',NULL,464,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1388,'Thursday Coin','\"Thursday is named after Thor, of course - everyone knows _this_ guy! And he\'s the god of thunder, sure-sure, but _also_ the god of storms, sacred groves, and the protection of humans! What a great guy!\" ~Kat','coin/thor',NULL,465,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1389,'Friday Coin','\"I know it\'s a language from however many thousands of years ago, but the idea of naming a god \'Frigga\' is so funny to me. Anyway, she\'s who Friday is named after, and she\'s a goddess of love and beauty and sex. SOMEHOW, it\'s always the women who are symbols of these things; never the dudes! (Gosh, I wonder why!) But it\'s like, gimme a hot sex man god, you know? Oh, uh, maybe leave that part out of the quote, though??\" ~Kat','coin/frigga',NULL,466,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1390,'Saturday Coin','\"Coming from Satyr Dice, you\'d super-think Saturday was named after Satyrs, but no! It\'s Saturn! B-O-R-I-N-G! Well, no, sorry, that\'s not true: Saturn\'s a super-interesting god of, like, liberation, time, wealth, and peace? And then somehow also agriculture?? Mythology! What a thing!\" ~Kat','coin/saturn',NULL,467,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1391,'Kat\'s Gift Package','\"Custom-made with your preferences in mind! ... ... What is it you like, again?\" ~Kat','box/florist','[[\"Chocolate\", \"katsGift/#/chocolates\"], [\"Gardening\", \"katsGift/#/gardeningSupplies\"], [\"Fishing\", \"katsGift/#/fishingGear\"], [\"Lava. I like lava.\", \"katsGift/#/lava\"]]',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,7),(1392,'Sunday Coin','\"When you think about it, isn\'t \'Sunday\', like, the LEAST creative name possible for a day? \'Oh, what should we call this one?\' Looks up. \'Sun... day?\' \'Sounds good to me!\'\" ~Kat','coin/sun',NULL,468,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1393,'Ace of Hearts','There\'s only one thing to do: go fish until you get a pair of \'em!','card/heart-ace',NULL,469,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,15,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1394,'Red Pear',NULL,'fruit/pear-red',NULL,NULL,508,9,NULL,257,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1395,'Ice \"Mango\"','This is not merely some ice-encrusted Mango! Ha! _Perish_ the thought!','fruit/mango-ice','[[\"Shatter\", \"iceMango/#/shatter\"]]',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,1),(1396,'Sour Cr